// Clue - AutomatonPartsClue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// DetailString :
"P2789782058" "You found a crate loaded with automaton parts.  This particular crate is full of enough parts to make one whole.....Longbow Agent?  This is a terrifying find, what is Nemesis up to?"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P1953684405" "You've seen this a dozen times.  Nemesis' men make some sort of hostage or bomb threat and then you go to the location only to find out it was a decoy, diversion or trap.<br><br>Well, you're sick of being led around by Nemesis.  You're going after the source of that transmission to beat some sense into the source of these problems."
// AcceptString :
"P841324759" "Investigate source of bomb threat transmission."
// SendOffString :
"P127764071" "Lord Nemesis works schemes within schemes within schemes.  This bomb threat seems like an obvious trap, perhaps too obvious.  Maybe going after the Nemesis terrorist himself will prove fruitful.  You might even get a shot at taking down Lord Nemesis himself!"
// ActiveTaskString :
"P3887410098" "Investigate broadcast location"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P2335178427" "You're sick and tired of being led around by Nemesis.  It's time to strike the threat at the source!  Go after the source of the Nemesis broadcast and bring him to justice!"
// TaskTitle :
"P2861364725" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>An Obvious Trap</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color deepskyblue><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P1605333386" "Just as you suspected.  Nemesis soldiers are preparing something here.  You wonder why they had to do whatever they're doing in the sewers."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P971562518" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>An Obvious Trap</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color deepskyblue><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>Well, you didn't get to take down Nemesis himself, just another one of his commanders.  While inside you were accused of trying to steal Flambeaux's glory, she attacked you in a frenzy!  You also uncovered a plot to build automatons that could replace humans.  What exactly is Nemesis up to?  Its clear that you were supposed to find all this though.  What's going on here?"

