// Task - AM_Hero_SL6-7_Task_10 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - SkyDragonClue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P4190302396" "Sky Dragon's Faith"
// DetailString :
"P555049734" "'{HeroName}, I knew you'd not desert the people of Paragon City.  I came here to make certain of this and to give you a chance to explain.  It seems I didn't need to, but it's good to have my good faith rewarded.  Let's find out who's really behind this."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - ZielenskiClue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P2149833632" "The Hasty Officer"
// DetailString :
"P438301971" "Oh {HeroName}, it's all my fault.  My parter, Officer Pello, told me to wait for backup...but as you can see I didn't listen.  Please help her, she's around here somewhere."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - PelloClue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P2021685270" "The Cautious Officer"
// DetailString :
"P2266359122" "I hadn't given up on you {HeroName}.  It's good to see you're no criminal.  Please, I beg you, look for my belov--err I mean my partner Officer Zielenski.  He's just so hasty!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P4052942545" "Just as you're thinking about returning to the scene of the crime you overhear an alert over your Paragon Police Department radio scanner:<br><br><color orange>ALERT!<br><br>{HeroName} has been seen fleeing from a second bank robbery in the company of the Freakshow and has fled to the sewers.  Officers are being dispatched to the scene.</color><br><br>Well, that's convenient.  This is a good chance to stop that imposter and show the PPD that you're not the one committing these crimes."
// AcceptString :
"P4230004651" "Clear your name."
// SendOffString :
"P3306199342" "It saddens you to believe faith in you could be lost so easily, but the reality is this sort of thing happens every day.  Heroes go bad, Villains redeem themselves, so you can't really blame them."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2683038580" "Clear your name"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P3047624510" "For the time being it's best to avoid the PPD and avoid confrontation until you can clear your name.  You set off to do just that."
// TaskTitle :
"P3977355617" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Wanted Poster With Your Face</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color deepskyblue><i>Hero Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P35411919" "Somewhere in these sewers is someone, or perhaps something pretending to be you.  You've got to reveal them for who they really are and clear your good name."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P899649049" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Wanted Poster With Your Face</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color deepskyblue><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You defeated an robotic copy of yourself that is built in a similar fashion to Nemesis automatons.  It even had powers very similar to your own.  However, you managed to clear your name after showing the Paragon Police Department and Longbow agents present that you weren't the one committing these crimes."

