// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_Hero_SL6-7_Task_12 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - DialogTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P3299209223" "<color orange>You see a radio on the ground. As you near it, you hear the sound of an old man beginning to speak coming from the speakers.</color><br><br>Ah, hello {HeroName}, it is a pleasure to meet you, face to face...in a manner of speaking. I've requested this personal...radio to be delivered to congratulate you on a job well done.<br><br>I am <color red>the Center</color>, leader of the Council."
// Answer Text :
"P1702842023" "You'll have to forgive me if I'm a bit suspicious of a fascist."
// Answer Text :
"P2410192562" "Congratulate me for now - you're next on my list."
// Answer Text :
"P2141214972" "(Turn off the radio)"
// Answer Text :
"P1544272653" "(Step away from the radio)"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P2727157919" "Of course, {HeroName}, you would not have gotten this far without suspicions. I wished to merely let you and Paragon know that this act was <i>not</i> of my doing.<br><br>I have been having some...issues with the men in the Council, stemming from Requiem. A powerful man...but a foolish one. There have been whispers that he plans to go back in time as well - something regarding the paths of power and a place called Cimerora.<br><br>But I am an old man and I linger. I merely wished to thank you for putting down this problematic group from the Council."
// Answer Text :
"P3427345322" "I'll take your thanks for what it's worth."
// Answer Text :
"P463327046" "I don't need your thanks."
// Page Page2 Text :
"P135535882" "<color orange>The Center laughs slightly, letting out a long sigh.</color><br><br>If only everyone in Paragon were as cordial as you, {HeroName}. I will bid you a farewell, and hope that perhaps when we meet, you will not try to punch this old man in the face.<br><br><color>The radio shuts off.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3542333078" "We'll see about that, Center."
// Page Page3 Text :
"P615212301" "<color orange>The Center lets out a dark laugh - the laugh of a man who has plans within plans for the future - before the radio shuts off.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P448839363" "Time to get out of this cavern."
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P1262126163" "You're a very focused individual, aren't you?<br><br>Tell me {HeroName}, is it so wrong to allow me to continue to exist? I am the man who stands between Paragon and Requiem. You do not know of his schemes - what you stopped just now is only the beginning.<br><br>I <i>bravely<i> risk my life to ensure that he is kept beneath my thumb. As much as you may hate to admit it, you and your city need me to protect it from monsters like Requiem."
// Answer Text :
"P1625888771" "Maybe you have a point. We'll see what the future holds."
// Answer Text :
"P3879691070" "I'll make a promise to you. Once Requiem is taken care of, I'm going after you next."
// Answer Text :
"P1576852868" "The city doesn't need monsters like you to defend it."
// Page PointPage Text :
"P1731019877" "Indeed we will see, {HeroName}. Who knows what the future holds? Who knows, I wonder...<br><br><color orange>The Center gives you a simple laugh - the laugh of a man who has plans within plans for the future - before the radio shuts off.</color>"
// Page Revenge Text :
"P3778686702" "<color orange>The Center laughs softly.</color><br><br>I'll hold you to that promise, {HeroName}. I'll be interested in seeing how exactly you plan on taking me down. Until then...take care.<br><br><color orange>The radio abruptly shuts off.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P1538773914" "I'll see you soon, old man."
// Page NeedMonsters Text :
"P3474425963" "A monster, am I? If I am the monster...then what does that make men like Requiem and Recluse?<br><br><color orange>The radio shuts off.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P1279523377" "(Leave the cavern)"
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P3533413614" "Now, you're probably wond-<br><br><color orange>Before the Center can deliver his speech, you shut off the radio. You don't have time to listen to fascists like him."
// Answer Text :
"P778525891" "Time to leave this place."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - DeadManJournal 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P600229770" "Dead Man's Tale"
// DetailString :
"P2711626313" "You found this journal off of a dead Council soldier. From his wounds, it would appear that he was attacked by his fellow comrades. You read over the journal, the last entry catching your eye... <br><br><color LightSeaGreen>I don't understand why we're being ordered to do this. The Center surely is not aware of what is happening - he cannot approve of this! I am certain that this has to do with the mad schemes of Requiem and Arakhn - they are surely using the Council to their own ends. If it comes down to it, I shall make my stand against these traitors. If I should die, at least the Center shall know that I stood for him and his rule! <br><br>- Archon Miller"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - Disturbance 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P2701819292" "Loud Noise"
// DetailString :
"P3027277696" "You've defeated the Council agent who was trying to plant the shadow seed and managed to reclaim the small object for yourself. As you do so, you hear the sound of something turning on towards the front of the cavern..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P3605483841" "The Nictus have been one of the larger looming threats over Paragon City and the world for quite some time, with the Council being one of the groups that seem to have an uneasy working relationship with them.<br><br>One thing is for certain - the Nictus cannot gain a foothold in this world, or else all is lost. If these seeds are planted, it could spell the beginning of the end for all of Paragon City! And you're the only person who can stop this from happening. There <i>is</i> the assassin Silent Blade, though just exactly how much she'll be able to do against this plot is unknown - or if she'll even uphold her end of Berkeley's deal."
// AcceptString :
"P2041828158" "Stop the Council from spreading the Nictus!"
// SendOffString :
"P12118133" "You've set your mind to the task - stopping the Council's made schemes and helping Silent Blade. You make your way to the cavern, where you'll do battle to help stop yet another threat to the entire world."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P71975408" "Save Paragon from the Council!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P3692827722" "Time is of the essence, the seeds may be planted at any moment by the Council!"
// TaskTitle :
"P1736605608" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Cloud of Odorous Smoke</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color deepskyblue><i>Hero Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P503273953" "You travel deep underground, following traces left by the Council soldiers. Time to end this mad plot of theirs."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P3178561391" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Cloud of Odorous Smoke</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color deepskyblue><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>The Council have been stopped, though there still is the threat of Requiem and the Center, looming over Paragon. For now, however, the city can rest easy - thanks to you."

